<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-05-09T14:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-05-09T14:24:00-05:00" n="115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                        <head>115. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                            to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d115fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                                Files, SOC 14-1 <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> VIET. Secret;
                                Operational Immediate. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_HTJ1">Heavner</persName> and cleared by <persName corresp="#p_REE1">Rice</persName>. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for POLAD.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="italic"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1963-05-09T15:24:00-04:00">May 9,
                                        1963, 3:24 p.m.</date></hi></dateline></opener>
                        <p>1066. Hue 4 to Dept.<note n="2" xml:id="d115fn2"><ref target="#d112">Document 112</ref>.</note> At your discretion suggest you urge
                                <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> take no repressive measures
                            against Buddhists, offer sympathy and funeral expenses to families of
                            demonstration victims, make any other appropriate gestures toward
                            restoration of order and amity between religious groups.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RD1"><hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>